{"id": "V8.13", "url": "https://leagueoflegends.fandom.com/wiki/V8.13", "date": "2018-06-27", "champions": [{"name": "Aatrox", "changes": [{"about": "General", "lines": ["Complete visual upgrade across all skins.", "New artwork for  Original Aatrox.", "Tweaked artwork for  Justicar Aatrox,  Mecha Aatrox, and  Sea Hunter Aatrox.", "New voice over.", "New lore."]}, {"about": "Stats", "lines": ["Base attack range increased to 175 from 150.", "Attack speed growth reduced to 2.5% from 3%.", "Base attack damage reduced to 60 from 70.", "Attack damage growth increased to 5 from 3.2.", "Armor growth reduced to 3.25 from 3.8.", "Health growth reduced to 80 from 85.", "Base health regeneration reduced to 5 from 6.5.", "Health regeneration growth reduced to 0.25 from 0.5."]}, {"about": "Deathbringer Stance (Innate)", "lines": ["Innate: Aatrox's next basic attack gains 50 bonus range and deals 8% - 16% (based on level) of the target's maximum health bonus physical damage, capped at 400 against monsters. Against enemy champions also Mutilates the target for 3 seconds, reducing all healing and shielding on them by 40%.", "Deathbringer Stance's cooldown is reduced by 2 seconds when Aatrox casts an ability or hits a champion with the edge of  The Darkin Blade.", "Static Cooldown: 25 seconds."]}, {"about": "The Darkin Blade (Q)", "lines": ["Active: Aatrox swings his greatsword in the target direction, striking enemies in a line. The Darkin Blade can then be reactivated twice within 4 seconds, with the second cast refreshing the timer. The second cast strikes enemies in a cone and the third in the target area.", "Each cast deals 15 / 30 / 45 / 60 / 75 (+64 / 68 / 72 / 76 / 80% AD) physical damage, increasing by 25% on the second cast and 50% on the third. The Darkin Blade deals 65% - 100% (based on level) damage to minions.", "Hitting enemies at the far end of the first two casts and the center of the third deals 50% bonus damage and  knocks up enemies for 0.25 seconds.", "Monsters take 10% AD bonus damage and are  knocked up for 0.5 seconds instead.", "Cooldown: 16 / 15 / 14 / 13 / 12 seconds."]}, {"about": "Infernal Chains (W)", "lines": ["Active: Aatrox smashes the ground in the target direction, creating a chain that stops on the first enemy hit, dealing 30 / 40 / 50 / 60 / 70 (+40% AD) physical damage, doubled against minions, and  slowing them for 1.5 seconds.", "If Infernal Chains hits a champion or large monster, they are chained to the impact area. If the chained enemy is still in the impact area after 1.5 seconds, they are  dragged to the center and take the same damage again.", "Cooldown: 18 / 17 / 16 / 15 / 14 seconds."]}, {"about": "Umbral Dash (E)", "lines": ["Passive: Aatrox heals for 15 / 16.25 / 17.5 / 18.75 / 20% of the premitigation-physical damage he deals, with a 33% effectiveness against non-champions.", "Additionally, Aatrox periodically stores a Umbral Dash charge, up to 2 stored at once.", "Active: Aatrox dashes in the target direction, gaining 15 / 25 / 35 / 45 / 55 bonus attack damage for 1.5 seconds.", "Umbral Dash can be cast during his other spellcasts without interrupting them.", "Cost: 1 charge.", "Cooldown: 3 / 2.5 / 2 / 1.5 / 1 seconds.", "Recharge: 20 / 18 / 16 / 14 / 12 seconds."]}, {"about": "World Ender (R)", "lines": ["Active: After a small delay, Aatrox unleashes his true demonic form for 12 seconds,  fearing nearby minions for 3 seconds, and for the first second gaining 120 / 180 / 240 bonus movement speed.", "While transformed Aatrox gains increased size and (20% AD) bonus attack damage, refreshing the bonus movement speed when out-of-combat with champions and turrets.", "Aatrox generates Blood Well equal to 15% - 50% (based on duration) of his maximum health over the first 10 seconds. Taking lethal damage during World Ender revives Aatrox over 3.25 seconds, during which he is  untargetable,  invulnerable,  slowed by 25%, unable to basic attack, cast abilities, or use summoner spells or item actives and consumes the Blood Well to recover the same amount of health.", "Cooldown: 160 / 140 / 120 seconds."]}]}, {"name": "Caitlyn", "changes": [{"about": "Headshot", "lines": ["Bug Fix: No longer interacts with  Stormrazor to deal extra damage while the  Stormrazor buff is inactive."]}, {"about": "Ace in the Hole", "lines": ["Bug Fix: Now correctly updates its range for the first use after leveling it."]}]}, {"name": "Camille", "changes": [{"about": "Hookshot", "lines": ["Base damage reduced to 60 / 95 / 130 / 165 / 200 from 75 / 120 / 175 / 210 / 255."]}]}, {"name": "Dr. Mundo", "changes": [{"about": "Masochism", "lines": ["Minimum bonus attack damage reduced to 30 / 45 / 60 / 75 / 90 from 30 / 50 / 70 / 90 / 110.", "Maximum bonus attack damage reduced to 60 / 90 / 120 / 150 / 180 from 60 / 100 / 140 / 180 / 220."]}]}, {"name": "Gragas", "changes": [{"about": "Drunken Rage", "lines": ["Cooldown changed to 5 seconds at all ranks from 8 / 7 / 6 / 5 / 4.", "New Effect: Now gains 50 bonus range for his next attack."]}]}, {"name": "Irelia", "changes": [{"about": "Ionian Fervor", "lines": ["Base on-hit damage per stack reduced to 1 - 12 (based on level) from 2.5 - 16.5 (based on level).", "On-hit AD ratio per stack changed to 4% bonus AD from 2% - 4% (based on level) AD.", "Bonus attack speed increased to 30% / 40% / 50% (based on level) from 20% / 30% / 40% (based on level)."]}, {"about": "Defiant Dance", "lines": ["Minimum base damage reduced to 10 / 25 / 40 / 55 / 70 from 10 / 30 / 50 / 70 / 90.", "Minimum AD ratio reduced to 50% AD from 60% AD.", "Maximum base damage reduced to 20 / 50 / 80 / 110 / 140 from 20 / 60 / 100 / 140 / 180.", "Maximum AD ratio reduced to 100% AD from 120% AD."]}, {"about": "Flawless Duet", "lines": ["Mark duration reduced to 5 seconds from 6."]}, {"about": "Vanguard's Edge", "lines": ["Mark duration reduced to 5 seconds from 6."]}]}, {"name": "Jarvan IV", "changes": [{"about": "Martial Cadence", "lines": ["New Effect: Now does a minimum of 20 da